The need for speed The Run fights across America.
Revision
Originally a problem-free race is transformed by a set of stupid mistakes of people who don't care about it in a routine morning shift at work.
It fulfills everyone's ambition to a certain extent, but it is useless if no one wants to do something more.
The new subtitled game The Run produced great expectations before its release.
He promised to take a new direction with the already old Need for Speed race series and to release a kind of game from playable games that would not only count with points.
So we were curious how the added passages will be in which the main hero comes out of his car and does what he wants.
As is already done in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what was expected.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the whole pulls down because of some useless faults that have already existed for several years.
These are not really mistakes but rather the expression of incomprehensible idleness on the part of developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are caught in the adventure where the main hero Jack has caracterial problems and to solve them starts to participate in illegal races across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than 50 races.
The result is that each race takes place on another route and the stages planned in different environments that differ quite well from each other and are interesting.
The player does not feel for a moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are pretty nice extravagance even if the graphic technical level is of the same type as the previous series.
I mean, it's not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in highly snowy mountains is very pleasant visually.
The tests are in addition from time to time accompanied by an atypical element.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly reduces your visibility.
Then in the mountains you have to be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
Next to that, the different races are well arranged behind each other.
There are only a few, but that is enough.
There are moments when you try to exceed the requested number of opponents (as in a classic race) and then you run against the clock (classic duel with the chronometer) and then you wait for another duel with an opponent.
From time to time you also have the police entering the game and trying to make the situation difficult for you.
The novelty is the off-vehicle passages.
It's more like an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away in front of someone and you have to help him by typing the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What is surprising is that there are fewer times of this type than you expect (to be concrete there are only three).
The result is this because this element is not likely to interfere and, in the context described above, is placed in the elements that enhance the game.
The driving pattern is in the tradition of previous games.
This means that at present there is nothing extraordinary, but it cannot be said to be negative.
As far as realistic simulation is concerned, you will have to go elsewhere.
But although one can find better in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of design of the races.
So it's all right.
Problems begin to appear after a while.
At the difference of the driving model, that of collisions is not yet perfect.
We don't expect this game to be a complicated distortion and collisions, but when you don't have, in a collision with any object, any idea of how your car behaves, it's not completely good.
During tight exceedances you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your self leaves in crazy voltigues.
Or you'll end up in crumbs.
Thanks to the restart system this is not really a problem but it really bothers you.
Rebooting is done so that when you broke the figure or you came out in the set the game will take you back to the last point on the route.
But you only have 5 restarts.
When you have used the 5 restarts you have to start the game again from the beginning.
So it's more of a tool, in case something doesn't go right, than something you can really count on.
Sometimes restarts do not help and the solution must be found by remembering from memory the piece of route in question.
The great thing about this game is that the same actions are found in the same places.
For example, there are certain turns that need to be made in a certain way otherwise it does not pass.
Otherwise you meet on a given location "civil" vehicles always in the same configuration as you arrived first, fifth, 5 seconds ahead or one minute late.
What makes you angry are situations when you easily see the opponent passing between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you have to either put yourself aside and converse or brake them.
It doesn't matter if you go in front of him because it's "calculated" in such a way that for the given situation it always happens very close to your nose.
Opponents have other advantages.
Throughout the game, you, you arrive in certain places, again without worrying about the time, and you always have the same opponent that precedes you in the same place.
This upsets the most at the end of the game when you roll on a long bridge in the opposite direction.
The opponent must pass in front of you at all costs.
When it passes in front of you it hides the view of other vehicles in the opposite direction and you collid a lot of times.
You can understand that the goal of this game is to do something captivating and full of adedalin, but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And that's a shame because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and places with so much action that you don't have time to follow everything that's happening.
And it doesn't matter if it's because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of the races is such that there's no chance of getting bored or anything else.
The original idea is the change of car during the races.
You have to pay attention to the gas pumps on the itineraries because you can change car there however most of the time the one you have is enough.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, big American cars for straight motorways and super sports cars with exotic corners on very technical pipes for example on yaw roads in the mountains.
And the mode of challenges, which are races in particular places you know of adventure, goes very well with the main diet of history.
You receive not only medals but also experience points that add to your profile, which is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, different objects begin to unlock:
This one connects on-line with the Autolog function which inter alia compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other functions in the community.
One of the most difficult blows to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (it looks like) where you drive in the dark on the tracks (it looks like).
Your speedometer tells you between 150 and 200 km/hour (presumably) and behind you arrives a metro train that sends you the car directly to the scrap.
In writing we had a discussion for a few days as to whether someone really thought about creating this game or whether the authors really think of us as fools.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is generally nice and in some cases really great.
What is bothering is that in more extreme situations, imaging does not hold the level and in some cases tragically.
This applies especially to accidents with a large number of participants when a fluid imaging is no longer useful to you.
The sound part is good and the track is of choice.
In order to please as many as possible and especially the young audience, a new sound track was created in the style of "I mix everything", but one can expect that no one will buy the game for music.
General Impression of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore really confused.
If the game didn't have these stupid mistakes we could safely say that this is the best NFS production in recent years.
But this game gives the impression that it is not finished.
The fun is really good but prepare yourself for mistakes to hit you in the eye with the strength of an aerodrome reflector.
Velvet students in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that link International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs from the higher schools and secondary classes.
The highlight of the festival was two concerts held on November 17.
"Charles University has an important part in this festival."
"Among the choirs there is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, on the committee of the festival sits the Rector Vaclav Hampl", says the leader of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the concert of the Choir des lycées et classes secondaires which takes place with free admission on November 17 from 2 pm on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the programme there is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening the concert "Etudiants de velour" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of the higher schools as well as that of the University Charles are performed.
The goal of the Festa Academica is not only to celebrate the International Student Day with dignity and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present to the public a choir music of the highest level and to develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organiser is the Union of Czech Choirs in cooperation with the Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, msical meetings, student happenings and other activities.
All information can be found on the Internet pages of the festival www.festaacademica.cz.
Vicenova, Ambassador to the European Union:
Czechs behave like negativists and Eurosceptics
"The Treaty of Lisbon has radically removed the balance between the institutions"
"I didn't expect such a hard war."
"It will last 5.6 years before the situation calms down and all the players get used to their new role", that is how Milena Vicenova began her presentation at the Faculty of Law the Czech Ambassador to the European Union.
When she managed to describe the different EU bodies and their relations in such an understandable and visible way, to the point that a large number of lecturers from the Faculty of Law at Charles University might envy her, she showed how serious she takes her wordto "understandable and openly about Europe" very seriously.
Mrs Vicenova paid tribute to the work of Herman Van Rompuye, the new Permanent President of the European Council.
"From the beginning, the critics sounded that he is bland, that it is a leather ring, that he cannot repeat any mission and I must say that he has taken the breath away from everyone because he holds his role to perfection".
"He is a man who knows how to listen to 27 member states, communicate well with them and has a clear vision of the direction to take of Europe."
She explained the new position of the High Representative for Foreign Affairs and Defence Policy as part of an answer to the question: "Who is in the European Union?" "What telephone number should I call?", so as an important step towards the uniqueness and greater legibility of the Union's policy vis-à-vis states, such as China or India.
No one wants to ban our syrecky (cooked cheese that smells very strong)
Mrs Vicenova also mentioned the agenda that the European Council has lived, lived and lived in the near future.
She called the Czech Presidency two years ago a success.
The Czechs have resolved the rising financial crisis, the gas crisis or have organised an Eastern Partnership Summit.
She described the fall as very negative and damaged the image of the Czech Republic.
The Czech representation in the EU is currently very busy.
In the words of Mrs L'Ambassadrice, "the activity has been in full swing" not only for the Presidency but also for the financial crisis which is still being resolved now.
In addition, we must approve the Union's new septum budget, which is becoming very complicated because of the current economic situation.
As it would appear that the budget will be thin and for savings, which branch will have the priority, which countries will be assisted the most, the least, everything is to be solved in future negotiations.
Ambassador recalled her slogans with which she arrived in Brussels "For an understandable Europe".
"I really don't like abbreviations, foreign words, jargons that nobody understands.
As the citizen must understand, it is true that in Brussels no one makes round or twisted pickles, bananas of different size or that no one has forbidden us to make syrecky".
She wants to make better use of the EU environment and see more Czechs in the European institutions.
A multi-speed Europe awaits us
According to the Ambassador the Czechs have the reputation of being Eurosceptics and people who see things only in their negative aspect more than positively.
Moreover, she is sorry to see such a small Czech representation in the European institutions.
The fault is, in her view, the result of several factors, such as the shyness of our candidates, their inability to write a cover letter and the lack of support from the Czech side.
In addition to a successful Czech Presidency, she then underlined the strength and cooperation of the Visegrad Group.
"Believe me, when the Pole, the Magyar, the Slovak come to me, this Frenchman says to me, 'Hey, what are you doing there, what is this Visegrad group doing again?' and he is not happy at all."
In the near future, according to Mrs Vicenova, the Member States are waiting for tough new rules on fiscal policy.
It is the concept of a two-speed Europe, if not a multi-speed Europe, that prevails rather than a "new European Federation".
"We have countries in the euro area and others outside the area."
"We have the Schengen area, we also have the Institute for Enhanced Cooperation".
In the first place it was said that co-operation between the countries that want it and those that do not want it remains in their corner."
"There will be a lot of such institutes and there will be a truly two-speed Europe," says Vicenova.
From this point of view it also appreciated the mission of the Czech Republic and Herman Van Rompuye to determine the basis according to which all themes having an impact on the EU should be discussed between all EU members and not just the same members of the Eurozone.
History of a brand:
IBM innovator begins the second century of its existence
If someone were to look for the word that expresses the IBM strategy as closely as possible, the closest would be "the long term".
For a large audience IBM is the symbol of the technological revolution, is a firm felt as very current and yet since its creation it has been a hundred years.
The basis for this long-term strategy was laid by the firm's first leader, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left the slogan that many global problems can be solved if people are willing to think.
His slogan "PENSE" has become the imprint around which the life of a giant future will develop (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began publishing in 1935).
This was the basis of Watson's carefully developed company culture.
For us IBM means a long-term thought of continuous movements directed towards the future.
IBM survived a hundred years because it always remained true to its core values and yet was not afraid to change all the others around it.
This has enabled us in our first century to transform technology, business and society.
We hope that in the second century we will reach even more lamented for the anniversary the current director of the firm Samuel J. Palmisano.
A well-prepared system
Watson, in the 1930s, began to look after his employees like Bata in the Czech Republic - IBM people were the only first American employees to have paid vacations, employer-paid insurance plus an elegant employee uniform and a well-developed system of awards for inventors and commercials.
In the same way IBM has a system of well-developed customer relations.
The company was at first brilliant in discovering talents- as one of the first firms to have abolished any form of discrimination and thus could have the choice.
The current plan is completely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy since it will be a woman - Virginia Rometty - who should replace Palmisano at the head of IBM.
She has been with IBM for thirty years and currently holds the position of Head of Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
IBM in recent years has done what is called jamy, online brain-storming from which come many future strategies and innovations.
It is not surprising that he has a lot of ideas - in the firm there are nearly 500,000 people who work.
