How to spot a lie
A look at recent headlines shows how widespread deception and lies are in everyday life.
Republican presidential candidate Herman Cain is busy exchanging allegations of sexual harassment with several women; each side accuses the other of lying.
The administrators of Penn State were accused of perjury for allegedly covering reports that a retired football coach sexually assaulted boys.
