At first, his music had a darker content and now it has become more positive.
What is the reason for this change?
It's interesting, because I think there are songs in the new album that look lighter, but there are also songs, like The End or Just Breathe qualified as very obscure songs, even though they may sound a little positive.
With both, when Ed played them for me, I cried when I listened to them and these are deeply obscure songs.
I think if you grow up and there's a trauma in your life and you lose to a parent or friend, these things start to influence your art and music and these songs, no doubt, represent that to me.
I also think that we can also be happy and even so we can make dark music.
