Fujimori hospitalized again for medical examinations
Former president Alberto Fujimori was hospitalized Tuesday in a public hospital to be evaluated for the loss of muscle strength he presents in the magpies, informed his family doctor.
Fujimori, 72, who is serving a sentence of 25 years in prison for human rights violations committed during his government (1990-2000) suffers from various conditions, including a language cancer for which he has been operated four times and which is under control.
Congressman Alejandro Aguinaga, his personal doctor, said for Canal N of television that Fujimori will be evaluated for three days in the National Institute of Neoplastic Diseases to determine the reason for the pain and the loss of strength in its lower limbs.
