Nintendo's spokesperson argued that, despite being in 3D, "Super Mario 3D Land" is a "accessible" video game that allows a fast and smooth game.
Álvarez claimed that "Super Mario 3D Land" contains two games in one: the first part is "simple" to hang less skilled users.
Once overcome, the most expert will be able to do a "second round" at game levels, which this time are more difficult.
