Property invaded by squatters for micro-festivals, evacuated
The invaders had appropriated 11 of the building's 13 apartments in Balmes, 51
The 12 occupants abandoned the property at noon yesterday without any resistance
Everything seems to indicate that the nightmare that the residents of 51 Balmes Street were living has come to an end.
Twelve people left the building they were illegally occupying at noon yesterday voluntarily and organised micro-festivals that despaired of the neighbours, by judicial order and without the need for police intervention.
At the end of the operation, the door lock was changed to prevent a repetition of the situation.
"From this day on there will be access control," said the administrator.
The squatters, who had invaded 11 of the building's 13 apartments - the rest were inhabited - carried away the electrical installation and part of the water, apart from painting the walls and leaving residues of all kinds, especially boxes of alcoholic beverages.
The first three apartments were the scene of mass festivals, which lasted up to two days and despaired the tenants.
Next to the building there is a discotheque, Balmes 51, which was also affected.
Its owner, Maria Pantinat explained for Europa Press that from the time the building was occupied its business fell a 80%.
